article.story: BOONE, N.C. -- — CJ Huntley's 27 points helped Appalachian State defeat Queens 65-53 on Tuesday night. Huntley added eight rebounds for the Mountaineers (2-2). Myles Tate added 19 points while shooting 5 for 9 (2 for 4 from 3-point range) and 7 of 10 from the free-throw line while he also had eight rebounds and three steals. Asjon Anderson finished with 13 points and two steals for the Royals (2-3). ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
